2. Link for Databricks APIs.
https://docs.databricks.com/api/azure/workspace/jobs/runnow
Use postman tool for sending requests using API calls

3. Databricks CLI documentation
https://docs.databricks.com/en/dev-tools/cli/index.html
 1. install python in your pc
 2. install databricks cli
 3. configure databricks ws
 4. you can ese the config fie on C\Users\<username> folder.
databricks cli allows you to manage various databricks resource like jobs, clusters
cli is built on top of databricks API



